## After installation is complete {#after-installation-is-complete}

After successful completion of the installation, the exchange will start in basic operating mode. Let's look at the basic steps to effectively manage the exchange:

1. Save and delete the save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt file from the server  
2. Log in to the admin panel  
3. Top up system crypto wallets (keepers and gas keepers)  
4. Top up a user through the admin panel  
5. Fill order books in trading pairs (place orders)  
6. Customize trading bot configurations  
7. Customize exchange interface  
8. Manage deposits and withdrawals

## Saving file save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt and its content {#saving-file-save_and_delete***.txt-and-its-content}

After a successful installation the file **save\_and\_delete\*.txt** will be saved on the server. It contains important technical data necessary to manage the exchange. To open the file and save the data, enter the following commands in the console:

cd /app/opencex/backend/  
ls

Find a file named save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt and enter the following command:

cat \<filename\>

The file will open in the console, select and save the file on your local computer. To delete a file enter the command:

rm \<filename\>

### File Contents {#file-contents}

The file contains blocks:

1. **Bot info.** Information about the bot's balance top up and bot's credentials.  
2. **Admin Info.** Superadmin credentials, master password and 2fa token for authorization in the admin panel.  
3. **BTC Info.** Information about the generated keeper ("hot wallet"), which was used for withdrawals from the exchange:   
- Keeper address. Multisig address of a hot wallet in the bitcoin network.  
- List of addresses from which the hot wallet was created, their private keys and seed phrases.  
4. **ETH Info.** Addresses of ETH and ERC-20 keeper("hot wallet"), gas keeper, and password to send withdrawals.  
5. **BNB Info.** Addresses of BNB and BEP-20 keeper("hot wallet"), gas keeper, and password to send withdrawals.  
6. **TRX Info.** Addresses of TRX and TRC-20 keeper("hot wallet"), gas keeper, and password to send withdrawals.

## Login to the admin panel {#login-to-the-admin-panel}

To enter the admin area for the first time, you will need superadmin credentials. Go to the url: **\<exchange domain\>/ADMIN\_BASE\_URL**, where **ADMIN\_BASE\_URL** \- parameter, specified during the installation. Login to the admin panel will open.  
![][image3]  
Enter the credentials of superadmin from **Admin Info** in the Username and Password fields. To enter a code in the OTP Token field, create a 2FA token in the Google Authenticator app.   
Find the 2fa token parameter in the file \- section **Admin info** \- parameter **2FA Token**: a link like otpauth://totp/admin%40exchange.net?secret=ALTDE5UFRRTQPV647OU50V56JQ65DCMY&.... Copy the value of the secret parameter, like **ALTDE5UFRRTQPV647OU50V56JQ65DCMY**. In the Google Authenticator app, select “Enter setup key”, enter the name, and paste the value in the “key” field. Leave the key type as standard \- By time. Once the setting is saved, a six-digit code will appear on the main screen of the app. The code is changed every minute. Enter the code from the application in the OTP Token field and click Log in.

## Work with hot wallets (keepers) {#work-with-hot-wallets-(keepers)}

### General Description {#general-description}

Keeper, aka "hot wallet" is a cryptocurrency address used for payouts. There are two types of keepers in the OpenCEX exchange engine:

1. Keeper for payouts. These keepers are used for withdrawals on the exchange. For each of the coin, a keeper is generated in the coin network during the installation of the exchange and saved in the file save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt. For tokens in various networks, such as USDT, the appropriate coins' keepers are used: USDT ERC-20 \- ETH keeper, USDT BEP-20 \- BNB keeper, USDT TRC-20 \- TRX keeper.   
2. Gas Keeper. A special keeper for sending a small amount of crypto to pay the network fee for accumulation tokens from user address. For example, when a user deposits USDT ERC-20 token into his wallet, about 0.002 ETH must be paid to the Ethereum network (amount depends on current load of Ethereum network) to accumulate it into a cold wallet. ETH is sent from the gas keeper to the user's address, after that the USDT token is accumulated on the cold wallet.

### Keepers top up {#keepers-top-up}

Keeper addresses are created during exchange installation and saved in save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt file as **Keeper address** and **GasKeeper** address. For correct work of deposits and withdrawals you need to have funds on **Keeper address** and **GasKeeper** addresses for coins and tokens withdrawal, as well as for fees on withdrawals and accumulations. Transfer the required amount of coins and tokens from your local or mobile wallet in the appropriate network to top up them.

### Notes {#notes}

1. ERC-20, BEP-20, TRC-20 token withdrawals require ETH, BNB and TRX on the Keeper address to pay network fees.  
2. TRX and TRC-20 tokens deposits require keepers addresses to be activated by the Tron network. To activate them, the addresses need to be topped up with a small amount of TRX.

## How to top up a user in the admin panel {#how-to-top-up-a-user-in-the-admin-panel}

Go to **Users** page, select user and click on action **Make Topup**   
![][image4]

Specify in the inputs on the page:

1. Amount \- enter the amount of currency  
2. Currency \- enter currency ticker(i.e. BTC)  
3. Password \- **Master Pass** value in the **Admin Info** block in the file save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt

When all fields are filled in click the **Do** button and the balance will be credited.

## Orderbook placement in trading pairs {#orderbook-placement-in-trading-pairs}

To fill the order book of a trading pair, for example BTC-USDT, you need to place AUTO orders at Buy and Sell side. AUTO order \- is an order with the price that changes every 60 seconds, the order price is set in % deviation from the external price (from Binance). To place an AUTO order you need to:

1. Specify the amount of currency to buy or sell.  
2. Specify the % deviation from the external price.  
3. Specify max or min price, above or below which the order price will not update.  
4. Click on the BUY or SELL button

AUTO orders are placed in the AUTO tab on the trade page. It is only available to technical users, e.g. superadmins. The AUTO order tab is activated in the user's profile in the admin panel.  
![][image5]

![][image6]![][image7]  
Orderbook without placed orders                   Orderbook with placed orders

## How to set up a bot in a trading pair {#how-to-set-up-a-bot-in-a-trading-pair}

Trading bots can be managed in the admin panel on the **Bots Configs** page. The list shows bot configurations created for trading pairs by default.  
![][image8]  
To edit the settings, click on the Edit “Pencil” icon. Here you can manage the bot:

1. Switch the bot off and on. To turn the bot off click the **Enabled** checkbox and click Save.  
2. Change the period of the bot's trading operations. The **Loop period** or **Min** and **Max period in seconds** when **Loop period random** is on are used for the bot operating period.  
   ![][image9]  
3. Change the amount of each trade. The **Min** and **Max order quantity** parameters are used to change the amount of trade.  
   ![][image10]  
4. Set the deviation from the external price of the trade. The **Ext price delta** parameter is responsible for this.  
5. Set the number of characters after the comma in the price and amount in the trades of the bot.  
   ![][image11]  
   **Symbol precision** \- decimals for the number of coins in the trade  
   **Quote precision** \- decimals for the trade price  
   ![][image12]

## How to customize the exchange interface {#how-to-customize-the-exchange-interface}

You can customize the interface, replace the logo and change the urls of social networks in the file **local\_config.js**. You can open and edit the file using the command in the console:

nano /app/opencex/frontend/src/local\_config 

### Setting up the color scheme of the exchange {#setting-up-the-color-scheme-of-the-exchange}

Color scheme settings are located in file **local\_config.js** in the array **themes**. You can specify colors in any of the supported formats: HEX, RGB, CSS W3.  
![][image13]

### Logo change {#logo-change}

Logo is changed in local\_config.js in the **logo** parameter. If this parameter is not set, the default OpenCEX logo is used.  
![][image14]  
Specify a direct link to the logo in the parameter to change it.  
![][image15]

### Social networks change {#social-networks-change}

To change the social networks on the main pages in the footer, specify your values in the following parameters in local\_config.js:  
![][image16]  
In the **link** field, specify only the nickname ("short name") of the page in the social networks.

### Applying settings {#applying-settings}

To apply changes in local\_config.js, save the file by pressing Ctrl+O in the console and exit the file with Ctrl+X. After that, update the frontend with the command:

cd /app/opencex/frontend/ ;  
git pull ;   
docker build \-t frontend \-f deploy/Dockerfile . ;  
cd /app/opencex/ ;  
docker compose up \-d \--force-recreate

After the command is executed, the frontend of the exchange will be updated and the changes will be applied.

## Work with deposits and withdrawals {#work-with-deposits-and-withdrawals}

### Working with crypto deposits {#working-with-crypto-deposits}

To deposit to an exchange, the user creates a crypto address for a deposit and sends the funds to it.  
![][image17]  
![][image18]  
After confirmation of the transaction by the cryptocurrency network, the deposit is credited to the user and accumulates on the cold wallet. The list of all user deposits on the exchange can be found in the admin panel in the **Top-ups & Withdrawals** section at **Crypto Topups** page. Available actions for deposits:

- **Force Deposit and Accumulate** \- starts a forced deposit and accumulate it to a cold wallet  
- **External Accumulation** \- starts accumulation to a third-party address not owned by the exchange.

### How to send a withdrawal {#how-to-send-a-withdrawal}

Sending a withdrawal requires:

1. The user creates and confirms the withdrawal by mail. The withdrawal gets the status Confirmed on the **Withdrawal Requests** page in the admin panel.  
2. The admin confirms the withdrawal by **Approve** action. Withdrawal gets Approved status.  
3. Go to the **\<coin\> Withdrawal Approve** page. Token withdrawals are on their network pages. For example, the approved withdrawal of USDT ERC-20 is on the Approve ETH page.  
   ![][image19]  
4. To start sending withdrawals to the network, click on **Process Withdrawals** action enter the master key(**Password** in save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt) for ETH, BNB and TRX networks. For bitcoin, enter the private key in the **Password** field of the **Manager** address (**BTC Info \- private data \- MANAGER \- private key** in save\_and\_delete\*\*\*.txt).
